  "original_title": "\u0d87\u0db8\u0dd9\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dd4 \u0db8\u0db1\u0dca\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0db4\u0ddc\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc3\u0dca \u0dbb\u0ddd\u0d9c\u0dd3\u0db1\u0dca \u0dad\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dd4\u0dab\u0dd4 \u0dbd\u0dd9\u0dc3 \u0d89\u0dc4\u0dc5\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "American monkeypox cases rise sharply",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Monkeypox cases are rising sharply in the United States, with more than 11,000 cases now reported, and the country's media and experts are blaming the Biden administration's response to contain the outbreak.",
        "According to the latest data from the US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC), 11,177 monkeypox cases have been reported across the country as of Friday.",
        "New York has the highest number of cases at 2,295. California reported 1,945 and Florida reported 1,085.",
        "Currently, the highest number of monkeypox cases in the world is reported from the United States."
      ],
